      "id": 24128,
      "name": "hathers",
      "username": "Hathers",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/h/bbe5ce/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2023-04-12T10:37:51.416Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I think it\u2019s related to the Time zone of the Location picked by the \u201cAdd Cool Routes to your rides\u201d feature and I don\u2019t think it\u2019s linked to any settings in the app.</p>\n<p>It\u2019s happened to me a couple of times importing into Garmin because it assumes you\u2019ve ridden in Death Valley or The Hague etc.</p>\n<p>Simple fix is to use a website like fit file tools to adjust the time of activity or just not use \u201cadd cool routes\u201d.</p>\n<p>I should add it only happens when you manually add the file into Garmin. Auto Import into Strava works fine.</p>",
